Red Bull star Max Verstappen made his intentions clear on Sunday with a dominant win at the Bahrain Grand Prix. The team's one-two to kick off the new season sent out a warning to the chasing pack, with Mercedes and Lewis Hamilton well off the pace. The Silver Arrows have effectively written off the current season as they work on a radical new design in the hope of making it back to the top. All efforts have been poured into the process, with even the issue of Hamilton's new contract taking a back seat. A P5 for Hamilton and a P7 for team-mate George Russell made for a disappointing weekend's work at Mercedes, while Aston Martin announced themselves among the race leaders in emphatic fashion as Fernando Alonso took a superb third place in Sakhir. With plenty to chew on after an intriguing first Grand Prix weekend, follow Express Sport's live updates below...